(45,'Andrew','Santino','images/Icons2/Icons2andrewSantino.jpg','Cool','https://www.instagram.com/cheetosantino/','https://www.youtube.com/@AndrewSantinoWhiskeyGinger/featured','link','link','Los Angeles','Andrew Santino, born on October 16, 1983, in Chicago, Illinois, is an American stand-up comedian, actor, and podcaster. He''s known for his quick wit, irreverent humor, and dynamic stage presence.  Santino''s comedic career gained traction with his appearances on various comedy shows and podcasts. He has a knack for delivering sharp observational humor, often commenting on pop culture, relationships, and everyday absurdities.  In addition to his stand-up, Santino has ventured into acting, with roles in television shows like "I''m Dying Up Here" and "Dave." His comedic talent translates well to the screen, allowing him to showcase his acting chops and comedic timing.  Santino is also a co-host of the popular podcast "Whiskey Ginger," where he engages in candid conversations with fellow comedians and other guests. This podcast has further endeared him to a wide audience.  With his distinct comedic style and versatile talents, Andrew Santino has solidified his place in the comedy world as both a stand-up comic and an entertainer in various media forms.'),
(46,'Bobby','Lee','images/Icons2/Icons2Bobby.jpg','Goofy','https://www.instagram.com/onlybobbylee/?hl=en','link','link','https://www.bobbylee.live/','Los Angeles','Robert Lee Jr. (born September 17, 1971) is an American stand-up comedian, actor, and podcaster. From 2001 to 2009, Lee was a cast member on MADtv, and he co-starred in the ABC single-camera sitcom series Splitting Up Together alongside Jenna Fischer and Oliver Hudson between 2018 and 2019. Lee has also appeared in the films Harold & Kumar Go to White Castle(2004), Pineapple Express(2008), and The Dictator(2012). He recently had a guest appearance as the cynical, burned-out Dr. Kang on FX on Hulu''s TV comedy series Reservation Dogs.  Lee co-hosts the podcast TigerBelly with his ex-partner, Khalyla Kuhn; he is also co-host of the podcast Bad Friends with Andrew Santino.');



